cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "QF-AgentOS: An Agentic Operating System for Quantum Finance"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - name: "QF-AgentOS contributors"
repository-code: "https://github.com/qf-agentos/qf-agentos"
license: Apache-2.0
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-07-15"
keywords:
  - quantum computing
  - quantitative finance
  - collateral optimisation
  - QAOA
  - QUBO
  - multi-agent systems
abstract: >
  QF-AgentOS is an open-source, provider-neutral platform that takes a financial
  optimisation problem, formulates it, builds strong classical baselines,
  identifies a quantum-compatible sub-problem, runs gate-model simulation (and,
  where authorised, real QPUs), deterministically verifies feasibility and
  quantum contribution, and honestly reports whether quantum technology should be
  used. Abstention and classical preference are first-class outcomes.
